{"api_url": "http://giottojs.org/ng/site/api/angular.json", "image": "http://giottojs.org/media/giottoweb/giotto.png", "slug": "api/angular", "modified": "2014-12-17T15:49:02", "site": {"media": "/media", "python_version": "3.4.2", "url": "http://giottojs.org", "year": 2014, "template_engine": null, "date": "2014-12-18T14-30-26", "name": "Lux", "lux_version": "0.1.2-alpha.1", "template": "partials/base.html"}, "title": "GiottoJS - AngularJS integration", "content_type": "text/html", "html_url": "http://giottojs.org/api/angular", "head": {"title": "GiottoJS - AngularJS integration", "twitter:card": "summary_large_image"}, "name": "api_angular", "html": {"main": "<div id=\"page-main\">\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<h2>GiottoJS - AngularJS integration</h2>\n</div>\n<div data-highlight>\n<p>GiottoJs comes with a small utility for facilitating integration with <a href=\"https://angularjs.org/\" title=\"AngularJS\">AngularJs</a>.\nOnce angular is loaded, a module can be created using the utility function</p>\n<pre><code>var ng = d3.giotto.angular;\n\nng.module(angular);\n</code></pre>\n<p>The function create a mdoule named 'giotto' by default. The call the module in a different name pass the module name as second parameter:</p>\n<pre><code>ng.module(nagular, 'mymodule');\n</code></pre>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"footer\">\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12 small\">\n<p>Library released under the <a href=\"http://opensource.org/licenses/BSD-3-Clause\">BSD License</a>.</p>\n<p>Copyright 2014 <a href=\"http://lucasbardella.com\">Luca Sbardella</a> and <a href=\"http://quantmind.com\">Quantmind</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>"}}